\intbl \ql \b Background\b0 \line The Durban University of Technology \'28DUT\'29 is a public higher education institution whose programmes have been accredited by the CHE. \line \line The Institution is currently applying for the accreditation of the Advanced Diploma in Technical and Vocational Teaching programme which will be offered in the contact mode of delivery from the Pietermaritzburg\'2C Indumiso campus and City Campus in Durban.\line \line The Institution has also applied for the accreditation of a Postgraduate Diploma in Higher Education programme which is still in process.\line \line The Institution is accredited to offer the following programmes\'3A \line - Bachelor of Education Honours in Technology Education - H\'2FH04\'2FE009CAN \line - Master of Education in Adult and Community Education - H\'2FH04\'2FE074CAN \line - Advanced Diploma in Adult and Community Education and Training Teaching-H\'2FH04\'2FE076CAN \line - Bachelor of Education in Senior Phase and Further Education and Training Teaching - H\'2FH04\'2FE091CAN \line -Postgraduate Diploma in Adult and Community Education and Training H\'2FH04\'2FE132CAN\cell \pard 

