\intbl \ql \b Summary of Evaluator Report\b0 \line The evaluator indicated that the programme in terms of Criterion 1 does not comply with the minimum requirements\'2C and that all the other Criteria to be assessed comply with the minimum requirements for accreditation and recommended that the programme should be accredited with conditions.\line \line According to the evaluator\'2C the programme is consonant with the Institution\'E2\'80\'99s mission. The evaluator found that the programme is coherently designed and articulates well with other relevant programmes. The evaluator\'2C however\'2C pointed out that the modules which constitute the programme indicate that ICT and Language of conversation are optional modules. This contrasts with the Policy on Professional Qualifications for Lecturers in TVET \'5BPPQLTVET\'5D which indicates that graduates in the Advance Diploma in TVET must be assessed as possessing basic conversational competence in at least one official African Language and in a Second language and ICT. The evaluator stresses that this must be corrected. \line \line The application indicates that the programme will give successful students access to the NQF level 8 Postgraduate Diploma in Technical and Vocational Education and Training or a Bachelor of Education Honours degree. Horizontally\'2C students can articulate to the Advanced Diploma in Management Sciences or the Advanced Diploma in Adult and Community Education and Training. \line \line With regards to Criterion 2\'2C the evaluator stated that the application accurately and sufficiently informs potential students of the programme and its admission requirements. The admission requirements comply with national legislative requirements \'28PPQLTVET Policy\'29. It is also indicated that the qualification must be linked to teaching specialisations relevant to the Technical and Vocational Education and Training context and that previous educator experience in respect of teaching and professional practice in business and industry will be considered for admission. The evaluator also indicated that the admission and selection of students are commensurate with the programme\'E2\'80\'99s academic requirements\'2C within a framework of widening access and equity. The selection criteria indicate that previous qualifications must be linked to teaching specialisations relevant to the Technical and Vocational Education and Training context. Students not in possession of the required qualifications for entry into the programme\'2C may apply for admission through the RPL route. However\'2C these applicants must either have proof of previous educator experience in the teaching of Technical and Vocational Education and Training subject specialisations or adequate industry experience. The evaluator was of the view that the Enrolment Plan must be realistic and manageable and that the proposed first-time enrolment of 50 may be optimistic. The evaluator proposes 35 students as the first intake. \line \line The evaluator found that the Teaching and Learning Strategy is appropriate for the institutional type. The strategy contains mechanisms to ensure the appropriateness of the teaching and learning methods\'2C which include mechanisms to monitor student progress and to evaluate the programme impact and effect improvements. \line \line As far as the monitoring of student progress is concerned\'2C use will be made of the Institutions Learning Management System \'28Blackboard\'29\'2C wherein lecturers will record students\'E2\'80\'99 assessment marks in the grade book for each module. The system has a tracking tool which will provide students with information on their performance thus enabling them to take steps to effect improvements during the year.\line \line The evaluator stated that different types of assessment for the programme are clearly indicated in the application as well as in the attached module information. The University Policy is attached\'2C however\'2C the assessment guideline for this programme need to be developed.  Since the TVET programme is new in higher education institutions\'2C therefore a plan to provide staff members with content and methodological upgrade for teaching this programme is vital. The university must be explicit about the plans for implementation. The application also includes general policies and procedures for internal assessment has been attached. \line \line Internal moderation is conducted to evaluate assessment practices\'2C approaches and mark allocations in order to provide developmental feedback to students. The evaluator pointed out that external moderators are academic peers who are independent experts whose appointment must be reviewed annually by Departments. Students who fail Continuous Assessment Subjects will be permitted to repeat assessments on Blackboard\'2Ftasks. Blackboard automatically tells the lecturer if the student is not logging on Blackboard and completing assessment tasks. The evaluator noted that the development of staff competence in assessment is not clarified.\line \line The Directorate recommends that the programme should be accredited with conditions.\cell \pard 

